author: The Politics Desk
description: In today’s edition, we have a deep dive into Sen. Josh Hawley’s effort to stake out ground for himself in the modern Republican Party.
title: Josh Hawley is ruffling GOP feathers as he stakes out his ground: From the Politics Desk

author: Andrea Mitchell
description: Finnish President Alexander Stubb, who has bonded with President Donald Trump over golf, gave NBC News an inside look at the White House meeting on Ukraine.
title: An unexpectedly pivotal figure in Ukraine negotiations speaks out

author: Ben Kamisar
description: A group of Texas Democrats are returning to the state House in Austin, where they will spend the night on the statehouse floor — the latest step in broader protest over Republican plans to redraw congressional districts in the state
title: More Texas Democrats plan to spend the night in the statehouse in protest amid redistricting fight

author: Jonathan Lloyd, NBC Los Angeles
description: The son of multi-division champ Julio César Chávez was wanted on an active warrant in Mexico, the DHS said after his arrest in Los Angeles in July.
title: Boxer Julio César Chávez Jr. deported to Mexico after LA arrest

description: Model Nadeen Ayoub will become the first woman to represent Palestine at the Miss Universe pageant.

description: The accounts point to the challenge of stopping or controlling the surge in fake images and misinformation targeting Spanish-speakers in the U.S., as AI technology advances.
title: What's behind the TikTok accounts using AI-generated versions of real Latino journalists?

description: In an interview with NBC News' Andrea Mitchell, Finnish President Alexander Stubb weighed in on the attempted peace negotiations between Ukraine and Russia. He likened the possibility of Ukraine ceding land to Russia to the U.S. giving up multiple states.
title: Finland president: Ukraine ceding land to Russia would be like U.S. giving up multiple states

author: Doha Madani
description: A man was arrested in Ocala, Florida, over the weekend after neighbors said he repeatedly aimed sprinklers at students with with disabilities
title: Man is accused of aiming sprinklers at students with disabilities waiting for a bus

description: The public should avoid eating certain frozen shrimp sold at Walmart due to concerns that the seafood may have been contaminated with radioactive material, the Food and Drug Administration said on Tuesday.
title: Walmart shrimp may have been exposed to radioactive material, FDA says

author: Mirna Alsharif
description: A federal appeals court decided to reverse the dismissal of a lawsuit filed by comedians Eric André and Clayton English in 2022 in which they claim their Forth Amendment rights were violated.
title: Eric André lawsuit over drug search at Atlanta airport revived by appeals court

author: Denise Chow
description: Roll out the cosmic welcome mat for our solar system’s newest resident: a never-before-seen moon orbiting Uranus
title: A new moon discovered orbiting Uranus is so small, you could walk it in two hours

author: Minyvonne Burke
description: Convicted murderer and rapist Grant Harding, known as the Devil in the Ozarks, broke out of an Arkansas prison after quietly collected items while working in the kitchen for months.

author: Michael Kosnar
description: The Justice Department is investigating whether Washington, D.C. police manipulated crime data to make the crime rates appear lower than they really are in the city, two senior law enforcement officials confirmed to NBC News
title: Justice Department is investigating whether D.C. police manipulated crime data

author: Freddie Clayton
description: A man wanted for war crimes sitting across the table from the leader of the country he invaded?
title: Trump's Ukraine diplomacy faces a new hurdle: Where can Putin and Zelenskyy meet?

author: Austin Mullen
description: Rhode Island prosecutor Devon Hogan Flanagan told police "you're going to regret this" during a confrontation that ended in her arrest which was caught on an officer's body camera, officials said Tuesday.
title: Video captures Rhode Island prosecutor warn that officers will 'regret this' as she's arrested at restaurant

author: Adam Noboa
description: The latest salvo in President Donald Trump’s campaign against mail-in voting arrived Monday, as he announced he wants to “lead a movement” against mail ballots and advocate instead for in-person and paper ballots, which he says are “faster, and leaves NO DOUBT, at the end of the evening, as to who WON, and who LOST, the Election.”Trump has criticized mail-in ballots since their rapid rise in 2020, when after years of slower growth they exploded as a key innovation of the Covid election
title: California's long ballot count may be Trump's next target in the war over voting

description: Democratic State Rep. Nicole Collier spent the night inside the State Capitol and called herself a "political prisoner" after refusing to agree to a law enforcement escort. NBC News' Ryan Chandler reports as Collier continues to stay on the House floor until the legislative body reconvenes later this week.
title: Texas Democrat spends night in State Capitol after refusing police escort

author: Max Gao
description: As this year’s U.S. Open kicks off, USTA President Brian Vahaly, a former top-100 player, opens up about his coming-out journey and his approach to being an LGBTQ leader in sports.
title: The first openly gay men's tennis player wants to make the sport more welcoming to queer athletes

description: President Trump says that American troops would not be sent to Ukraine as a security guarantee for any potential peace deal to end the conflict with Russia. NBC News' Yamiche Alcindor reports on the latest developments as the president says arrangements for a possible meeting between Ukrainian President Zelenskyy and Russian President Putin are underway.
title: Trump rules out sending U.S. troops to Ukraine as security guarantee for peace deal

author: Doha Madani
description: A pair of influencers known for their food reviews caught the moment they were injured on Saturday after a car hit the restaurant where they were filming.
title: Food influencers injured after car slams into restaurant as they filmed a review

author: Zoe Malin
description: The best dusters are from Amazon, Swiffer, Oxo, Mr. Siga and more. Expert tips for how to dust your home, how often to dust and why dust can trigger allergies.

description: There was a muted response from Israel after Hamas said it had agreed to the latest proposal for a ceasefire in Gaza and to free the remaining hostages.

author: Steve Kopack
description: The U.S. government aims to take an equity stake in Intel, Commerce Secretary Howard Lutnick said Tuesday morning.“We should get an equity stake for our money, so we’ll deliver the money which was already committed under the Biden administration,” Lutnick told CNBC.

author: Matt Lavietes
description: Authorities are searching for a Texas man that was "mistakenly" released from jail before he was set to serve a 5 year state prison sentence

description: Hurricane Erin is expected to grow as it moves over the Atlantic through the week, causing dangerous rip currents, heavy rain and strong winds along the East Coast.

author: Matt Lavietes
description: Actor Aubrey Plaza addressed the death of her late husband in an interview released on Tuesday, marking the first time she's publicly spoken at length about the loss

author: Amy Delgado
description: The city known for lavish shows, endless buffets and around-the-clock gambling saw an 11% drop in tourism compared to the same time last year.

description: After a weekslong standoff, Texas Democratic lawmakers who fled the state to slow a Republican plan to redraw voting maps have returned to the state's capitol. Republicans wasted no time passing the new congressional maps out of committee and barred the Democrats from leaving the chamber without a police escorts assigned to watch them around the clock. NBC’s Ryan Chandler reports for TODAY.
title: Texas Democratic Lawmakers Return to Cheers and Consequences

description: Hurricane Erin is fueling evacuation orders in North Carolina after pounding Puerto Rico with heavy rain and flooding. The storm is now moving almost parallel to the Eastern seaboard, threatening states from Florida to Massachusetts with coastal flooding and dangerous rip currents. NBC’s Aaron Gilchrist reports and TODAY’s Dylan Dreyer tracks the storm’s path.
title: Hurricane Erin Fuels East Coast Evacuations: Where Is It Headed?

author: Elizabeth Robinson
description: Trump meets with Ukraine’s Zelenskyy and other European leaders at the White House.

description: Ukrainians are expressing relief that their country has broad diplomatic support from Europe as President Donald Trump tries to mediate a peace deal with Russia. Despite frequent Russian attacks, many Ukrainians appear pleased that President Volodymyr Zelenskyy successfully navigated a meeting with Trump without it backfiring again. NBC’s Richard Engel reports for TODAY.
title: Ukrainians Express Relief After Zelenskyy’s White House Meeting

author: Daryna Mayer
description: While the Kremlin smarted, a sense of relief swept through Ukraine and across Europe after Zelenskyy's summit with President Trump.

author: Andrew Greif
description: The Dallas Cowboys have not reached the NFC Championship in 30 years. But their lack of on-field success has not hindered their popularity and profits.

description: The Air Canada strike has ended after flight attendants reached a tentative agreement with the airline, both parties said early Tuesday."The Strike has ended," the Canadian Union of Public Employees said in a Facebook post, advising its membership to "fully cooperate with resumption of operations."
title: Air Canada, flight attendants reach tentative deal to end strike

author: Molly Hunter

description: The senator from Missouri is increasingly focused on appealing to working-class voters — even if that means criticizing his party or teaming up with Democrats.
